WEBVTT

00:01.084 --> 00:03.921
<i>Previously on "The Rookie"...</i>
Thanks again
for helping me with

00:03.921 --> 00:05.005
the transitional housing
paperwork.

00:05.005 --> 00:06.381
What are you on?
It's just a little Oxy.

00:06.381 --> 00:07.424
You get my report
on Mack Daniels?

00:07.424 --> 00:09.426
Are you sure this is the way
you want things to go?

00:09.426 --> 00:10.511
He'll get fired.

00:10.511 --> 00:11.970
Do you know why
they call me "La Fiera"?

00:11.970 --> 00:14.181
You were caught in a narco
gunfight with baby Diego,

00:14.181 --> 00:16.016
grabbed a gun and laid
everyone to waste.

00:16.016 --> 00:17.309
When it comes to your child,

00:17.309 --> 00:19.645
there is nothing you won't do
to protect them.

00:19.645 --> 00:21.271
Feeling okay?

00:21.271 --> 00:22.773
♪♪

00:23.482 --> 00:24.608
[ "The Cock That Walked" plays ]

00:24.608 --> 00:26.652
[ Siren wailing ]

00:26.652 --> 00:31.907
♪♪

00:31.907 --> 00:33.242
Maggie:
What happened?

00:33.242 --> 00:34.660
Nolan: My son was born with
Tetralogy of Fallot.

00:34.660 --> 00:36.620
He collapsed 13 minutes ago.

00:36.620 --> 00:38.288
He had five surgeries on his
heart before his first birthday.

00:38.288 --> 00:39.873
Well, that's a severe case
of TOF.

00:39.873 --> 00:41.166
Has he been short of breath
recently?

00:41.166 --> 00:43.043
Nothing I noticed.
Eh, Abigail?

00:43.043 --> 00:44.419
He didn't mention anything.

00:44.419 --> 00:45.629
He would have mentioned it,
right?

00:45.629 --> 00:47.047
What ‐‐
What's happening to him?

00:47.047 --> 00:48.549
Well, the surgeries
he had as a baby

00:48.549 --> 00:50.676
helped to improve
the blood flow to his lungs,

00:50.676 --> 00:53.262
but as a patient gets older,
those procedures can cause

00:53.262 --> 00:54.805
the valve between the heart
and the lungs to leak.

00:54.805 --> 00:56.306
It's called ‐‐

00:56.306 --> 00:58.100
Pulmonary valve
regurgitation.

00:58.100 --> 00:59.810
When your baby's sick,
you become an expert.

00:59.810 --> 01:02.187
[ Grunting ]
What's going on?

01:02.187 --> 01:04.022
Henry,
we're at the hospital.

01:04.022 --> 01:06.233
You ‐‐ You fainted at home
and again in the car ride over.

01:06.233 --> 01:07.734
You're gonna be okay, kiddo.

01:07.734 --> 01:09.069
Doctor's gonna
take great care of you.

01:09.069 --> 01:10.487
That's right.
My name is Maggie,

01:10.487 --> 01:11.738
and we're gonna start with
a full battery of tests.

01:11.738 --> 01:13.532
Dad?
Yeah?

01:13.532 --> 01:14.658
You haven't called me kiddo
since I was little.

01:14.658 --> 01:15.742
♪ What if what we do
does not define us? ♪

01:15.742 --> 01:17.744
♪ Define us ♪

01:20.163 --> 01:22.416
Look, being in a hospital
in uniform is like asking

01:22.416 --> 01:24.084
every rando to make
their problems yours.

01:24.084 --> 01:25.335
We'll be in and out.

01:25.335 --> 01:27.045
I just want to make sure
he's okay.

01:27.045 --> 01:28.630
Brought you breakfast.

01:28.630 --> 01:30.757
Oh. Thank you.

01:30.757 --> 01:32.843
Um, not much
of an appetite right now,

01:32.843 --> 01:33.844
but I'll hang onto that.

01:33.844 --> 01:35.304
How's Henry?

01:35.304 --> 01:37.431
Uh, just waiting on some,
uh, final test results.

01:37.431 --> 01:39.141
[ Cellphone ringing ]
Excuse me.

01:39.141 --> 01:41.018
[ Elevator bell dings ]
[ Cellphone beeps ]

01:43.854 --> 01:46.273
Morning, sir.
Good morning.

01:46.273 --> 01:47.691
Can I get a minute
with Officer Nolan?

01:47.691 --> 01:49.526
Of course, sir.

01:49.526 --> 01:51.695
Text me
if you need anything.

01:51.695 --> 01:53.530
Right. Thank you.

01:54.364 --> 01:56.700
Sir, I realize as a rookie,
I don't get vacation days ‐‐

01:56.700 --> 01:59.494
Stop.
Family trumps everything.

01:59.494 --> 02:01.121
You're exactly where
you're supposed to be.

02:01.121 --> 02:02.414
I squared it
with the captain.

02:02.414 --> 02:05.208
You're fine, so...
sit down.

02:08.170 --> 02:09.629
[ Sighs ]

02:09.629 --> 02:12.424
[ Indistinct conversations ]

02:12.424 --> 02:14.468
How's that new
garage conversion coming?

02:14.468 --> 02:17.929
John, we don't need
to do small talk.

02:17.929 --> 02:19.514
We can just sit here.

02:19.514 --> 02:21.016
Thank you.

02:21.016 --> 02:22.184
Woman over P. A.:
<i>X‐ray tech to Radiology.</i>

02:22.184 --> 02:24.061
<i>X‐ray tech to Radiology.</i>

02:24.061 --> 02:26.521
That's crap.
I gave you a deposit.

02:26.521 --> 02:27.731
I expect it back.

02:27.731 --> 02:29.274
[ Cellphone beeps ]
[ Sighs ]

02:29.274 --> 02:32.277
I just lost the venue for
Lopez's bachelorette party.

02:32.277 --> 02:33.820
Where'd you have yours?

02:33.820 --> 02:35.697
I eloped so I wouldn't
have to have one.

02:35.697 --> 02:37.866
Well, if you were planning one
for a friend?

02:37.866 --> 02:41.078
I try and stay out of
no‐win situations like those.

02:41.078 --> 02:43.664
Cuts down on the drama.
Great.

02:43.664 --> 02:45.916
[ Indistinct conversations ]

02:45.916 --> 02:47.959
Concealed weapons,
12 o'clock.

02:47.959 --> 02:49.336
What'd I tell you?

02:49.336 --> 02:50.837
We haven't even been here
five minutes ‐‐

02:50.837 --> 02:52.422
we're already getting pulled
into trouble.

02:52.422 --> 02:54.132
Gentlemen,
you know the drill.

02:54.132 --> 02:56.051
Concealed carry permits,
please.

02:56.051 --> 02:58.637
Ah, ah, ah, slowly.

02:58.637 --> 03:00.138
So, what?
They're recruiting cops

03:00.138 --> 03:02.224
from the modeling schools now?

03:02.224 --> 03:03.892
I can't tell
which one of you's prettier.

03:03.892 --> 03:06.436
Clearly me.
Who's your client?

03:06.436 --> 03:08.271
Sorry.
Not at liberty to say.

03:08.271 --> 03:10.107
We signed a non‐disclosure.
[ Scoffs ] Yeah.

03:10.107 --> 03:11.400
That's not really
how this works.

03:11.400 --> 03:12.776
[ Indistinct conversations ]

03:12.776 --> 03:15.112
It's La Fiera.
Great.

03:15.112 --> 03:17.072
Now we're gonna be here
all day.

03:17.072 --> 03:18.281
Are we cool?

03:18.281 --> 03:19.366
Yeah.

03:19.366 --> 03:22.369
[ Indistinct conversations ]

03:22.369 --> 03:23.620
What do you think
she's doing here?

03:23.620 --> 03:25.664
Nothing good.

03:25.664 --> 03:27.666
Please stop.

03:27.666 --> 03:31.086
I don't want to know the gender
until the baby's born.

03:31.086 --> 03:32.671
I spend my days trying to
figure things out.

03:32.671 --> 03:34.131
I just want one mystery
in my life

03:34.131 --> 03:36.466
that I'm not
trying to solve.

03:36.466 --> 03:38.427
Okay, but we can still have
a list of names on deck, right?

03:39.761 --> 03:41.304
Fine.

03:41.304 --> 03:44.057
But for every WASPy name
you pick,

03:44.057 --> 03:45.684
I'm gonna pick something
so Mexican,

03:45.684 --> 03:47.602
you'll never be able
to spell it.

03:47.602 --> 03:51.481
[ Chuckles ] Okay.
Uh, if it's a boy, Thatcher.

03:51.481 --> 03:55.777
I'll raise your Thatcher
to a Cuauhtémoc.

03:55.777 --> 03:58.905
And if it's a girl,
Xochitl.

03:58.905 --> 04:01.324
And we're not picking a name
until B‐day.

04:01.324 --> 04:03.160
Doing it now
could jinx us.

04:03.160 --> 04:04.911
I had no idea you were
this superstitious.

04:04.911 --> 04:06.413
I'm not.

04:06.413 --> 04:08.498
I just wear a talisman
a drug lord gave me

04:08.498 --> 04:12.794
to keep evil spirits away
from my unborn child.

04:12.794 --> 04:15.338
Better safe than sorry.

04:15.338 --> 04:17.257
[ Cellphone ringing ]

04:17.257 --> 04:19.259
♪ Oh, ah ♪

04:19.259 --> 04:21.428
[ Cellphone beeps ]
Ah.
Hey, Sarge, what's up?

04:21.428 --> 04:23.096
Sgt. Grey:
<i>La Fiera's back in town.</i>

04:23.096 --> 04:24.681
<i>Harper and Tim just spotted her</i>
<i>at Shaw Memorial.</i>

04:24.681 --> 04:26.683
I'm at Shaw Memorial.
What floor?

04:26.683 --> 04:28.852
<i>Eight.</i>
<i>They have eyes on her.</i>

04:28.852 --> 04:30.353
Can you reassign them to me,
sir?

04:30.353 --> 04:32.189
Until I figure out
what's going on?

04:32.189 --> 04:34.149
<i>Sure. I'll notify the on‐call</i>
<i>watch commander.</i>

04:34.149 --> 04:36.443
Thanks.
[ Cellphone beeps ]

04:36.443 --> 04:38.153
I gotta step out
for a quick sec.

04:38.153 --> 04:40.322
What? No, no.
W‐We're up next.

04:40.322 --> 04:42.991
I'll be right back,
I promise.

04:42.991 --> 04:44.534
[ Sighs ]
♪ Whoo! ♪

04:44.534 --> 04:46.995
Ms. Lopez?
We're ready for you.
[ Chuckles ]

04:46.995 --> 04:49.414
[ Radio beeps ]
Control, show us Code 6
at Shaw Memorial.

04:49.414 --> 04:52.000
Suspect needs medical attention
before transport to booking.

04:52.000 --> 04:54.753
Dispatch: <i>Copy that.</i>
We were pulling you over
for a rolling stop.

04:54.753 --> 04:56.755
I still don't get
why you sped up.

04:56.755 --> 04:58.590
It was involuntary.

04:58.590 --> 05:00.884
When I get anxious,
my body always chooses flight.

05:00.884 --> 05:02.385
And if you wouldn't
have run,

05:02.385 --> 05:03.720
we just would've
given you a ticket.

05:03.720 --> 05:05.347
But now we gotta book you
for evading police

05:05.347 --> 05:07.349
and a hit‐and‐run.
Damn my DNA.

05:07.349 --> 05:09.267
Morning. [ Sighs ]
Who have you brought me today?

05:09.267 --> 05:10.727
This is Billie Park.

05:10.727 --> 05:13.063
She decided to start off our day
destroying city property.

05:13.063 --> 05:14.397
I cut my arm.

05:14.397 --> 05:15.440
Let's take a look.
Could you...

05:15.440 --> 05:16.900
Yeah. [ Grunts ]

05:16.900 --> 05:18.026
♪ If it's a good time you want,
you know I got it ♪

05:18.026 --> 05:19.611
[ Handcuffs rattle ]
♪ I got it ♪

05:19.611 --> 05:21.196
♪ 100‐dollar bills keep
spilling out of my wallet ♪

05:21.196 --> 05:23.240
Ooh. Yeah.
Right over here.

05:23.240 --> 05:25.617
♪ Like MJ, like game six,
I'm fresh to death ♪

05:25.617 --> 05:27.661
Yeah, you're gonna need
stitches.

05:27.661 --> 05:28.870
Better give me a few.

05:28.870 --> 05:29.996
Alright.
♪ Whoo! ♪

05:31.581 --> 05:33.416
Well, I'm gonna head
to the cafeteria.

05:33.416 --> 05:35.418
I didn't get any breakfast.
What? You?

05:35.418 --> 05:36.545
You never miss a meal.

05:36.545 --> 05:38.338
Eh ‐‐ Are you calling me fat?

05:38.338 --> 05:40.048
Yeah.
That's what I'm doing.

05:40.048 --> 05:41.299
Yeah, well, your girl
raided the kitchen

05:41.299 --> 05:42.551
before she left for school,

05:42.551 --> 05:44.010
and there was literally
nothing left.

05:44.010 --> 05:45.804
Yeah, I'm sorry.
I know that I kind of...

05:45.804 --> 05:47.347
foisted Tamara onto you.

05:47.347 --> 05:51.268
Look, you know that I respect
that she needs help,

05:51.268 --> 05:52.602
but any idea how long
she's gonna be

05:52.602 --> 05:53.687
camped out on our couch?

05:53.687 --> 05:55.981
Not long. I hope.

05:55.981 --> 05:57.524
I've been having a hard time
getting in touch

05:57.524 --> 05:59.442
with the local
housing assistance program.

05:59.442 --> 06:01.820
They give grants to teens
who age out of foster care,

06:01.820 --> 06:03.738
you know, help them get into
transitional apartments,

06:03.738 --> 06:05.490
but every time I call

06:05.490 --> 06:07.367
to check on the status
of her application,

06:07.367 --> 06:09.494
they have these
crazy‐long hold times.

06:09.494 --> 06:12.831
Well, I mean, we are gonna
be here for a minute, so...

06:12.831 --> 06:15.917
Good point.
[ Both chuckle ]

06:15.917 --> 06:19.212
[ Sucks teeth ]
[ <i>Line ringing</i> ]

06:19.212 --> 06:22.424
Automated voice:
<i>Thank you for calling Angels</i>
<i>West Extended Care Program.</i>

06:22.424 --> 06:24.801
<i>There are...three ‐‐</i>
<i>callers ahead of you.</i>

06:24.801 --> 06:26.094
Only three?
[ <i>Muzak plays</i> ]

06:26.094 --> 06:27.220
Ooh!
This is my lucky day.

06:27.220 --> 06:30.015
Hey.
<i>Our</i> lucky day. Yeah.

06:30.015 --> 06:32.267
[ <i>Muzak continues</i> ]

06:35.812 --> 06:37.355
I thought it was nothing.

06:37.355 --> 06:39.900
I've been tired,
but we've been really busy with,

06:39.900 --> 06:41.693
uh, my new job.

06:41.693 --> 06:45.488
[ Sighs ] Everything's just
been fine for so long.

06:45.488 --> 06:48.033
I guess I just stopped
thinking about it.

06:48.033 --> 06:49.117
Sarah:
I don't buy it.

06:49.117 --> 06:50.660
Mom. [ Chuckles ]

06:50.660 --> 06:52.704
I think this is
some kind of elaborate plan

06:52.704 --> 06:53.913
to reunite me
and your father,

06:53.913 --> 06:54.914
"Parent Trap"‐style.

06:54.914 --> 06:56.291
[ Chuckling ]
God, no.

06:56.291 --> 06:57.542
You guys are
so much happier apart.

06:57.542 --> 06:59.210
Fair enough. Hi.

06:59.210 --> 07:01.921
Hi.
The day we dreaded.

07:01.921 --> 07:04.924
Such a drama queen.

07:04.924 --> 07:08.553
Okay.
It's gonna be okay.

07:08.553 --> 07:10.347
Are you in pain?

07:10.347 --> 07:12.182
No, I just can't
catch my breath.

07:12.182 --> 07:13.600
Results are in.

07:13.600 --> 07:14.851
It's the pulmonary valve,
isn't it?

07:14.851 --> 07:17.145
Yes, the valve is failing.

07:17.145 --> 07:18.355
He'll need surgery
to repair it.

07:18.355 --> 07:19.648
Is it dangerous?

07:19.648 --> 07:22.525
It can be.
You have a choice.

07:22.525 --> 07:24.903
We can do a minimally invasive
procedure

07:24.903 --> 07:27.489
known as a percutaneous
pulmonary valve replacement

07:27.489 --> 07:29.407
that's relatively safe.

07:29.407 --> 07:33.453
Recovery time is about a week,
but the fix won't last.

07:33.453 --> 07:35.830
You'll need to have open heart
surgery in about five years.

07:35.830 --> 07:38.458
Or they could do the open heart
surgery right now, right?

07:38.458 --> 07:41.920
Yes. He'll need to have
a live tissue valve replacement

07:41.920 --> 07:42.962
that could last decades.

07:42.962 --> 07:44.506
Well, what are we waiting for?

07:44.506 --> 07:46.257
Sign me up for not wanting
to go through this again

07:46.257 --> 07:47.300
anytime soon.

07:47.300 --> 07:48.927
N‐Not so fast.

07:48.927 --> 07:51.304
We're talking about
a much riskier surgery, right?

07:51.304 --> 07:52.806
Yes.

07:52.806 --> 07:55.392
Henry could have a heart attack
on the operating table.

07:55.392 --> 07:57.769
He could bleed into
his chest cavity

07:57.769 --> 08:00.522
or have other complications
after we close him up.

08:00.522 --> 08:02.440
But his age ‐‐

08:02.440 --> 08:04.984
mortality rate for a procedure
like this is, what, 2%, 3%?

08:04.984 --> 08:09.406
No, because of factors
related to his prior surgeries,

08:09.406 --> 08:13.660
the risk of mortality is higher,
about 20%.

08:13.660 --> 08:16.538
Okay.
That's a lot to process.

08:16.538 --> 08:18.873
Well, you'll need to
make a decision quickly.

08:18.873 --> 08:22.085
Your heart is very unstable
right now.

08:22.085 --> 08:23.628
Nice meeting you.
You, too.

08:23.628 --> 08:25.630
Thanks for
taking care of him.

08:25.630 --> 08:27.132
Mm‐hmm.

08:29.217 --> 08:30.635
Obviously, you're having
the procedure

08:30.635 --> 08:32.762
that doesn't have a 20% chance
of killing you.

08:32.762 --> 08:35.682
I‐I think we take the safer bet
and call it a day.

08:35.682 --> 08:38.393
What if that's not
what I want?

08:38.393 --> 08:40.353
It's my choice.
I'm an adult.
Henry ‐‐

08:40.353 --> 08:42.605
Okay, we don't have to decide
this instant.

08:42.605 --> 08:45.483
I mean, let's just take
a breath, take a minute,

08:45.483 --> 08:49.195
uh, walk through it,
and go over your options.

08:49.195 --> 08:51.448
♪♪

08:51.448 --> 08:53.199
Sandra.

08:54.868 --> 08:55.994
[ Speaking Spanish ]

08:55.994 --> 08:57.078
Look at you.

08:58.788 --> 09:00.707
Motherhood suits you.

09:00.707 --> 09:02.667
Didn't think you'd risk your
son's life coming back to L. A.

09:02.667 --> 09:04.878
Actually, I'm here
to save my son.

09:04.878 --> 09:06.963
Well, his knee, anyways.

09:06.963 --> 09:08.381
Diego, what happened?

09:08.381 --> 09:09.966
It was so cool.
I was playing <i>fútbol</i>

09:09.966 --> 09:12.052
and went full Carlos Vela,
and pop ‐‐

09:12.052 --> 09:14.387
partial tear of my ACL,
but I got the goal.

09:14.387 --> 09:17.557
He's having surgery today ‐‐
top sports doctor in the world.

09:17.557 --> 09:19.434
And that's the only reason
you're here in L. A.?

09:19.434 --> 09:20.727
Of course.

09:25.023 --> 09:26.691
It was good to see you.
You, too.

09:26.691 --> 09:28.485
Good luck
with the surgery.

09:28.485 --> 09:29.819
Uh...

09:31.196 --> 09:33.990
[ Elevator bell dings ]

09:33.990 --> 09:35.658
So, what are you really
doing here?

09:35.658 --> 09:39.370
<i>Hermana,</i>
don't be so suspicious.

09:39.370 --> 09:41.790
Surely, you have better things
to worry about.

09:41.790 --> 09:43.291
You're here
for the baby, no?

09:43.291 --> 09:46.086
I was, until I got a call
about you,

09:46.086 --> 09:47.837
and now my fiancé
is cursing us both.

09:47.837 --> 09:49.089
How is Wesley?

09:49.089 --> 09:50.924
He must be so excited.

09:50.924 --> 09:52.467
Relax.

09:52.467 --> 09:53.885
I learned his name
when I was dropping off

09:53.885 --> 09:56.554
the present for your baby.

09:56.554 --> 09:58.473
And I see you're wearing
the ribbon.

10:01.476 --> 10:03.728
I really hope you're only here
for your son.

10:03.728 --> 10:05.313
'Cause if you're
up to something,

10:05.313 --> 10:06.689
it's not gonna end well.

10:06.689 --> 10:08.525
For you or Diego.

10:08.525 --> 10:12.862
♪♪

10:12.862 --> 10:15.657
[ <i>Muzak plays</i> ]

10:15.657 --> 10:17.951
Oh, that's what you're having
for <i>breakfast?</i>

10:17.951 --> 10:19.536
Hey, this happens to have 8%

10:19.536 --> 10:21.746
of the recommended daily
allowance of riboflavin.

10:21.746 --> 10:23.164
She's all yours.

10:23.164 --> 10:25.083
Thank you.

10:25.083 --> 10:26.876
Control, suspect is
medically cleared.

10:26.876 --> 10:28.461
We are en route
to lower booking.
Dispatch: <i>Copy.</i>

10:28.461 --> 10:30.004
Woman: <i>Angels West.</i>
<i>How can I help you?</i>

10:30.004 --> 10:31.673
‐Yeah.
‐Yeah!

10:31.673 --> 10:33.591
Oh, she's running again.
Oh, damn it!

10:33.591 --> 10:35.593
Oh! Sorry!

10:35.593 --> 10:38.263
10‐15 is running.
Foot pursuit at Shaw Memorial.

10:38.263 --> 10:40.014
♪ Free ppls livin' any place
I know of ♪

10:40.014 --> 10:42.851
♪ Free ppls in another location
but the ♪

10:42.851 --> 10:45.395
♪ Free ppls hate the ppl
who want to become ♪

10:45.395 --> 10:46.604
♪ Free ♪

10:46.604 --> 10:48.565
♪♪

10:48.565 --> 10:50.942
Turn around.
Put your hands up.

10:50.942 --> 10:52.735
Something's wrong.

10:58.741 --> 11:00.952
[ Breathes sharply ]

11:00.952 --> 11:02.745
Mnh.
[ Handcuffs clinking ]

11:02.745 --> 11:05.999
Yeah.
No more running.

11:05.999 --> 11:07.584
What happened?

11:07.584 --> 11:09.335
You had severe abdominal pain
and passed out.

11:09.335 --> 11:11.337
Doctor ordered a CT scan
and an X‐ray.

11:11.337 --> 11:14.132
Uh, no, I don't want that.
I bet,

11:14.132 --> 11:16.050
'cause you've got a stomach full
of drug balloons.

11:17.635 --> 11:19.345
No, I don't.

11:19.345 --> 11:22.432
Okay. Billie, we are trained
police officers.

11:22.432 --> 11:24.225
You had a ticket to Ibiza
in your pocket.

11:24.225 --> 11:26.644
You ran from the cops,
and now you appear to have

11:26.644 --> 11:28.313
serious intestinal issues.

11:28.313 --> 11:29.981
We're gonna have
proof soon,

11:29.981 --> 11:31.357
so just tell us what kind
of drugs they are.

11:31.357 --> 11:33.484
Can't you just
leave me alone?

11:33.484 --> 11:35.195
Please?
No.

11:35.195 --> 11:36.404
And right now,
getting busted for drugs

11:36.404 --> 11:38.573
is the least
of your problems.

11:38.573 --> 11:39.949
The real concern is
if one of those drug balloons

11:39.949 --> 11:41.576
in your stomach bursts.

11:41.576 --> 11:43.578
Look, if it's filled with
cocaine or meth,

11:43.578 --> 11:45.872
your heart rate will
rapidly accelerate

11:45.872 --> 11:48.249
until full cardiac arrest,
and then muscles in your chest

11:48.249 --> 11:50.210
will tear apart
as you slowly suffocate.

11:50.210 --> 11:52.921
Yeah, and if it's heroin,
fentanyl, or an opioid,

11:52.921 --> 11:54.923
you'll ride high for a while,
then you'll crash.

11:54.923 --> 11:57.133
You'll lose all your
motor functions, and you will ‐‐

11:57.133 --> 11:59.093
well, you'll vomit
until you're dead.

11:59.093 --> 12:01.471
[ Chuckles ]
Well, then we're fine.

12:01.471 --> 12:03.848
It was just Molly.
Those are happy pills.

12:03.848 --> 12:05.850
MDMA?
Yeah.

12:05.850 --> 12:07.227
How much?

12:07.227 --> 12:09.771
Uh...four condoms.

12:09.771 --> 12:12.190
Like...80 pills each?

12:12.190 --> 12:14.609
Okay.
I'll tell the doctor.

12:14.609 --> 12:16.277
[ Radio beeps ]
Control, notify
on‐call narcotics.

12:16.277 --> 12:17.528
We have a kilo‐plus mule
in custody.

12:17.528 --> 12:18.905
What's wrong?

12:18.905 --> 12:20.698
Look, if even one of
those packets burst,

12:20.698 --> 12:22.450
you'll start to
hallucinate.

12:22.450 --> 12:24.327
Your body temperature will rise
to 105 degrees,

12:24.327 --> 12:25.703
and you'll die from
a heat stroke

12:25.703 --> 12:27.413
during the worst nightmare
of your life.

12:28.748 --> 12:30.500
There you are.

12:30.500 --> 12:32.418
Sorry.
It was a work emergency.

12:32.418 --> 12:33.878
Is that true?

12:33.878 --> 12:35.630
I want no part of this.

12:35.630 --> 12:37.590
I had to beg to get
our appointment rescheduled.

12:37.590 --> 12:39.133
The OB will see us
in 15 minutes.

12:39.133 --> 12:40.051
[ Cellphone chimes ]
You're the best.

12:40.051 --> 12:41.219
Thank you.
Yes!

12:41.219 --> 12:42.679
My buddy came through.

12:42.679 --> 12:43.846
We're having
your bachelorette party

12:43.846 --> 12:46.266
at his sports bar
on Sunset.

12:46.266 --> 12:48.601
Uh, I'm ‐‐ That's ‐‐
I'm joking.

12:48.601 --> 12:50.270
That's not ‐‐
I would never.

12:50.270 --> 12:53.189
I got surveillance footage
of La Fiera from security.

12:53.189 --> 12:55.358
After you left her,
she snuck over to the ICU.

12:57.318 --> 12:59.529
That's Mack.
Who?

12:59.529 --> 13:01.114
Uh, Mack Daniels.

13:01.114 --> 13:03.574
Uh, he worked undercover
until I got him suspended

13:03.574 --> 13:05.034
for drug use on the job.

13:05.034 --> 13:06.286
He's facing
criminal charges.

13:06.286 --> 13:08.204
And here he is,
talking to a major narco.

13:08.204 --> 13:09.789
That can't be a coincidence.

13:09.789 --> 13:10.999
Let's go ask him.

13:10.999 --> 13:12.709
♪♪

13:12.709 --> 13:15.378
Can you reschedule our
appointment for a little later?

13:15.378 --> 13:17.297
Thank you.
I love you.
[ Sighs ]

13:17.297 --> 13:20.383
♪♪

13:21.592 --> 13:22.927
Oh, damn it.

13:22.927 --> 13:24.345
Mack.
What are you doing here?

13:24.345 --> 13:26.139
[ Sighs ] Working.
Private security.

13:26.139 --> 13:28.683
For Sandra de la Cruz?
No.

13:28.683 --> 13:30.184
So, who's your client?

13:30.184 --> 13:31.811
I don't know.
Really?

13:31.811 --> 13:33.062
That's how you want to
play this?

13:33.062 --> 13:34.814
When you're clearly 5‐50?

13:34.814 --> 13:36.190
Tim: Come on, Mack.

13:36.190 --> 13:37.400
You don't need any more
trouble right now.

13:39.861 --> 13:41.696
I'm working for
Tomás Madrigal.

13:41.696 --> 13:43.614
[ Exhales sharply ]

13:43.614 --> 13:46.159
You do know
who that is, right?

13:46.159 --> 13:48.953
The largest drug kingpin
in Southern California.

13:48.953 --> 13:51.914
He is subject in multiple
ongoing investigations.

13:51.914 --> 13:53.332
Yeah, he's dying of cancer.

13:53.332 --> 13:54.709
He only has a few days
left on Earth,

13:54.709 --> 13:56.794
and I lost my ability
to be picky

13:56.794 --> 13:59.088
when my buddy Bradford here
snitched me out.

13:59.088 --> 14:01.299
I lost my paycheck
and my pension.

14:01.299 --> 14:03.301
I'm up to my eyeballs
in lawyer bills,

14:03.301 --> 14:05.053
not to mention the alimony
and child support

14:05.053 --> 14:06.637
I'm gonna owe
once Beth divorces me.

14:06.637 --> 14:08.222
So, your solution is to go
work for the enemy?

14:08.222 --> 14:10.058
I'm not breaking any laws.

14:10.058 --> 14:11.684
I'm just standing watch,
making sure that nobody

14:11.684 --> 14:13.227
interrupts an old man's
final moments.

14:13.227 --> 14:14.854
Not even La Fiera?

14:14.854 --> 14:16.397
We saw Sandra de la Cruz
come by.

14:16.397 --> 14:18.649
What was she doing here?
Paying her respects.

14:18.649 --> 14:21.861
The old man was sleeping.
She said she'd stop by later.

14:21.861 --> 14:23.196
Mack, is there a problem?

14:25.031 --> 14:26.866
No.
No problem, Mr. Madrigal.

14:26.866 --> 14:29.702
I'm just, uh, catching up with
some former colleagues.

14:29.702 --> 14:31.746
Do it on your own time.

14:31.746 --> 14:33.122
We're paying you to keep your
mouth shut and watch the door.

14:33.122 --> 14:35.917
[ Chuckles ]
No, your old man's paying me.

14:35.917 --> 14:37.835
And I'm gone
the second he is.

14:37.835 --> 14:39.295
Oh, that reminds me.

14:39.295 --> 14:41.339
He, uh...
He was asking for you earlier.

14:41.339 --> 14:42.381
Why didn't you call me?

14:42.381 --> 14:44.092
<i>X‐ray tech to Radiology.</i>
Whoops.

14:44.092 --> 14:46.469
<i>X‐ray tech to Radiology.</i>

14:46.469 --> 14:48.262
Mack.

14:48.262 --> 14:49.972
You sure pissing off the next
El Jefe is a smart move?

14:49.972 --> 14:51.641
He's a punk wannabe.

14:51.641 --> 14:53.017
That kid'll drive the whole
operation into the ground

14:53.017 --> 14:54.435
within six months.

14:54.435 --> 14:56.395
Now, if you don't mind,
I, uh...

14:56.395 --> 14:57.855
I gotta get back to work.

14:57.855 --> 14:59.190
<i>Med tech to CTU.</i>

14:59.190 --> 15:00.441
[ Scoffs ]

15:00.441 --> 15:02.360
<i>Med tech to CTU.</i>

15:02.360 --> 15:04.487
You alright?
He went after you pretty hard.

15:04.487 --> 15:06.405
Yeah, I'm fine.

15:06.405 --> 15:08.741
So, clearly, La Fiera is here to
meet with the dying drug lord.

15:08.741 --> 15:10.535
We just have to
find out why.

15:10.535 --> 15:13.704
You know I happen to be
wiretap certified, right?

15:13.704 --> 15:15.289
Team work makes
the dream work, baby.

15:15.289 --> 15:17.208
<i>Transition team to OR 2.</i>

15:17.208 --> 15:19.252
[ Beeps ]
<i>Transition team ‐‐ OR 2.</i>

15:19.252 --> 15:22.505
Alright, so I can listen
for exactly two minutes.

15:22.505 --> 15:24.423
If they are not talking about
anything illegal,

15:24.423 --> 15:27.260
I have to wait and shut it off
for 30 seconds,

15:27.260 --> 15:28.427
and then I can turn it
back on

15:28.427 --> 15:30.179
and start the two‐minute clock
again.

15:30.179 --> 15:31.305
I wish we had video
inside the room

15:31.305 --> 15:33.307
instead of just the hallway.

15:33.307 --> 15:35.309
Eh, we're lucky the judge
granted the audio surveillance,

15:35.309 --> 15:38.354
but we don't need a warrant
to film in the hallway,

15:38.354 --> 15:41.149
and I managed to find
an interesting angle.

15:41.149 --> 15:42.567
Nicely done.

15:42.567 --> 15:44.318
Thank you.

15:44.318 --> 15:46.070
Now we just wait
for something to happen.

15:47.155 --> 15:49.532
It's been hanging over my head
my whole life, okay?

15:49.532 --> 15:51.534
It's stupid to do
the short‐term fix.

15:51.534 --> 15:53.661
I don't want to be here again
in a few years.

15:53.661 --> 15:56.080
I want this behind me
for as long as possible.

15:56.080 --> 15:57.498
I get that.
We get that.

15:57.498 --> 15:59.750
It's just with a minimally
invasive procedure,

15:59.750 --> 16:02.211
you'd be on your feet again
in a week.
Yeah.

16:02.211 --> 16:04.380
Recovery from open heart
surgery, that'll take months.

16:04.380 --> 16:05.798
You'll have to
give up the job.

16:05.798 --> 16:07.633
Then I give it up.

16:07.633 --> 16:09.302
Alright?
It's ‐‐ It's my life.

16:09.302 --> 16:11.179
It's my choice.

16:11.179 --> 16:13.347
Hey, it's ‐‐
it's gonna be okay.

16:13.347 --> 16:16.559
Alright?
We're gonna grow old together.

16:16.559 --> 16:19.353
I'll have dentures,
and you'll still be

16:19.353 --> 16:21.022
as beautiful as you are
right now.

16:21.022 --> 16:23.274
When you were born,

16:23.274 --> 16:24.692
your skin was blue.

16:24.692 --> 16:27.195
♪♪

16:27.195 --> 16:29.197
I've never been so scared
in my life.

16:29.197 --> 16:31.199
Until now.

16:31.199 --> 16:32.992
I know it feels like
the worst thing

16:32.992 --> 16:34.577
is to have another surgery
in five years,

16:34.577 --> 16:36.537
but, Henry, that is not
the worst thing.

16:36.537 --> 16:38.497
[ Gasps ]
Henry?

16:38.497 --> 16:39.624
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]
What's happening?
What's happening?

16:39.624 --> 16:40.666
Henry!
What's happening?

16:40.666 --> 16:41.792
Doctor!

16:41.792 --> 16:44.170
Henry?
Doc!

16:44.170 --> 16:45.213
Hey, buddy.
Just breathe.

16:45.213 --> 16:46.505
Hey, just breathe,
nice and easy.

16:46.505 --> 16:48.382
Hey. Henry, Henry.
He was fine.

16:48.382 --> 16:50.134
Everybody step away, please.

16:50.134 --> 16:51.302
He was fine,
and then all of a sudden ‐‐

16:51.302 --> 16:54.055
He's in V‐fib.
Back, please.

16:54.055 --> 16:56.766
Charge to 200.
I got rails
on this side.

16:56.766 --> 16:58.768
Please, buddy.

16:58.768 --> 17:00.353
[ Beeping continues ]

17:00.353 --> 17:01.729
Chest is clear.

17:01.729 --> 17:03.648
Charging.

17:03.648 --> 17:04.941
[ Beeping continues ]

17:04.941 --> 17:06.025
[ Paddles whine ]
Down.

17:06.025 --> 17:07.610
[ Beeping continues ]

17:07.610 --> 17:09.362
Okay, everyone, clear.

17:09.362 --> 17:10.613
[ Thump ]

17:10.613 --> 17:12.949
♪♪

17:12.949 --> 17:15.534
[ Monitor beeping ]
[ Gasps ]

17:15.534 --> 17:17.078
Okay, he's stable for now.

17:17.078 --> 17:18.162
Let's prep him for surgery.

17:18.162 --> 17:19.705
[ Speaking indistinctly ]

17:19.705 --> 17:20.998
What's the decision?

17:20.998 --> 17:22.750
♪♪

17:22.750 --> 17:23.626
We have to do
what he wants.

17:23.626 --> 17:25.253
No, we don't.

17:25.253 --> 17:26.712
No, now's the time
to play it safe

17:26.712 --> 17:28.589
a‐and do
the least invasive surgery.

17:28.589 --> 17:30.132
After that, we'll reassess.

17:30.132 --> 17:31.342
Maggie:
What's the answer?

17:31.342 --> 17:33.010
Woman: ...tube.
Prepping your meds. 120...

17:33.010 --> 17:35.096
What do you think?

17:35.096 --> 17:37.223
I don't know.

17:37.223 --> 17:39.267
[ Henry wheezing ]

17:39.267 --> 17:41.018
We do what he wants.

17:41.018 --> 17:42.645
Anything else will be
a betrayal.

17:42.645 --> 17:44.063
♪♪

17:44.063 --> 17:45.773
Sarah, he'll be okay.

17:45.773 --> 17:47.942
[ Wheezing continues ]

17:47.942 --> 17:50.570
♪♪

17:50.570 --> 17:52.154
Do the open heart surgery.

17:59.662 --> 18:03.416
Mm. Now we just have to wait
until she poops.

18:03.416 --> 18:05.585
Who said being a cop
isn't livin' the dream?

18:05.585 --> 18:07.211
Just look on
the bright side.

18:07.211 --> 18:08.671
We scored
a solid drug bust.
Mm.

18:08.671 --> 18:11.340
And I bet we can get her
to give us her supplier

18:11.340 --> 18:13.009
with the right pressure.

18:13.009 --> 18:15.136
Alright, well, I am gonna make
good use of my time.

18:15.136 --> 18:17.555
[ Chuckles ]
[ <i>Line ringing</i> ]

18:17.555 --> 18:19.640
Automated voice:
<i>Thank you for calling Angels</i>
<i>West Extended Care Program.</i>

18:19.640 --> 18:22.935
<i>There are...46 ‐‐</i>
<i>callers ahead of you.</i>

18:22.935 --> 18:24.353
[ <i>Muzak plays</i> ]
Okay, well,

18:24.353 --> 18:25.730
you keep the faith.

18:25.730 --> 18:28.065
I'll, uh, check on
the narco detective.

18:28.065 --> 18:29.358
[ Radio beeps ]
Control, please be advised

18:29.358 --> 18:32.236
that we are still 10‐6
at Shaw Memorial.

18:32.236 --> 18:34.739
Was there, um, any updates
from the narcotics table?

18:34.739 --> 18:36.407
Dispatch: <i>Negative.</i>

18:36.407 --> 18:38.200
[ Sighs ]

18:39.619 --> 18:40.870
[ <i>Muzak continues</i> ]

18:40.870 --> 18:42.663
[ Siren wails in distance ]

18:42.663 --> 18:47.793
♪♪

18:47.793 --> 18:48.878
What are you watching?

18:48.878 --> 18:50.129
Uh, just a TikTok.

18:50.129 --> 18:52.965
Of our living room?
Are ‐‐

18:52.965 --> 18:54.884
Are you spying on Tamara?

18:54.884 --> 18:57.386
No! No. I'm just trying out
a home security system.

18:57.386 --> 18:59.680
You are a lying liar
who lies.

18:59.680 --> 19:01.849
Okay. Fine.

19:01.849 --> 19:05.478
My Swarovski Baby Yoda figurine
disappeared, okay?

19:05.478 --> 19:07.063
Eh ‐‐ Okay.
And so, what?

19:07.063 --> 19:08.856
You installed a nanny cam

19:08.856 --> 19:11.317
because you <i>think</i> she stole
your stupid toy?

19:11.317 --> 19:13.861
Okay, two things ‐‐
it's not stupid ‐‐

19:13.861 --> 19:15.655
it's amazing.

19:15.655 --> 19:16.781
And it's not a toy ‐‐

19:16.781 --> 19:19.909
It's a rare collectible
of sorts.

19:19.909 --> 19:21.452
I can't believe
you would do this.

19:21.452 --> 19:24.080
Look, Tamara would never
take advantage of us.

19:24.080 --> 19:25.998
I know her.
Eh, do you?

19:25.998 --> 19:28.042
I mean, yeah, she seems like
a great person,

19:28.042 --> 19:29.669
and I love that
you <i>want</i> to trust her,

19:29.669 --> 19:31.462
but it doesn't really
change the fact

19:31.462 --> 19:33.631
that she's been,
you know...
What?

19:33.631 --> 19:36.300
...living on the streets.

19:36.300 --> 19:38.094
There's no telling what
she had to do to survive.

19:38.094 --> 19:40.262
[ Sighs ] Why didn't you
talk to me about this?

19:40.262 --> 19:42.973
Why didn't you talk to me before
inviting the Artful Dodger

19:42.973 --> 19:45.559
to live in <i>our</i> apartment?

19:45.559 --> 19:46.894
Baby Yoda is missing.

19:46.894 --> 19:49.689
No, he's not, okay?
I broke him.

19:49.689 --> 19:51.649
It was an accident.
I'm sorry.
[ Breathes sharply ]

19:51.649 --> 19:53.818
I was gonna replace it
before you even noticed.

19:53.818 --> 19:56.570
I never thought that you would
blame a traumatized teenager.

19:56.570 --> 20:01.200
♪♪

20:02.576 --> 20:03.869
Where's my headset?

20:03.869 --> 20:05.913
Officially,
only I can listen,

20:05.913 --> 20:09.500
but I'm allowed to use
a translator if needed,

20:09.500 --> 20:11.711
and my Spanish is
a little rusty today.

20:11.711 --> 20:14.213
<i>Gracias.</i>

20:14.213 --> 20:15.798
Tomás:
<i>Mijo, when I am gone ‐‐</i>

20:15.798 --> 20:16.590
Cesar: <i>Come on...</i>

20:18.467 --> 20:20.845
<i>I don't want to go.</i>
<i>Believe me.</i>

20:20.845 --> 20:22.263
There's nothing illegal about

20:22.263 --> 20:23.556
talking to your father
about dying.

20:23.556 --> 20:24.974
We gotta turn it off.

20:24.974 --> 20:27.184
Hold on.
We still got a minute.

20:27.184 --> 20:30.563
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

20:30.563 --> 20:31.897
[ <i>Door opens</i> ]

20:31.897 --> 20:33.524
Sandra:
[ <i>Speaking Spanish</i> ]

20:33.524 --> 20:35.234
Cesar: <i>Who let you in here?</i>
<i>Get out.</i>

20:36.444 --> 20:38.863
<i>Señor Madrigal,</i>
<i>with all due respect,</i>

20:38.863 --> 20:40.322
<i>I would like</i>
<i>a word in private.</i>

20:40.322 --> 20:43.743
Tomás: <i>I admire your</i>
<i>persistence, Señora de la Cruz.</i>

20:43.743 --> 20:45.494
<i>Mijo, please.</i>

20:45.494 --> 20:46.537
<i>Papá, she has no business</i>
<i>here ‐‐</i>

20:46.537 --> 20:48.205
<i>Cesar.</i>

20:48.205 --> 20:50.249
[ <i>Wheezes</i> ]
<i>Out.</i>

20:50.249 --> 20:52.042
[ <i>Wheezes</i> ]

20:54.462 --> 20:57.840
<i>I don't wish to create trouble</i>
<i>between you and your son,</i>

20:57.840 --> 21:00.342
<i>but it's important</i>
<i>that we speak.</i>

21:00.342 --> 21:02.136
<i>I came here</i>
<i>to ask for your...</i>

21:02.136 --> 21:05.681
[ Loud whirring ]

21:05.681 --> 21:06.807
What the hell?

21:06.807 --> 21:08.976
Hey.
Turn that off.

21:08.976 --> 21:11.312
How much you gonna pay me?
What?

21:11.312 --> 21:12.938
The other lady ‐‐
she paid me to buff.

21:12.938 --> 21:14.106
You gonna pay me to stop?

21:14.106 --> 21:17.693
Shut it down. Now.

21:17.693 --> 21:19.195
[ Whirring stops ]

21:21.739 --> 21:23.741
[ Sighs ] She knows
we're up on a wire.

21:23.741 --> 21:25.367
No doubt.
But with Madrigal dying,

21:25.367 --> 21:27.328
this conversation
has to happen today.

21:27.328 --> 21:29.580
Sandra: <i>I am aware of</i>
<i>my son's limitations,</i>

21:29.580 --> 21:32.124
<i>as I'm sure you are aware</i>
<i>of your son's.</i>

21:32.124 --> 21:33.876
<i>It's what we have in common.</i>

21:33.876 --> 21:35.252
<i>We are not like our sons.</i>

21:35.252 --> 21:37.463
<i>It's a shame.</i>
<i>Not necessa‐‐</i>

21:37.463 --> 21:38.464
[ Beeping ]
[ Sighs ]

21:38.464 --> 21:40.174
That's time.

21:41.342 --> 21:43.093
Part of me feels bad
for those boys.

21:43.093 --> 21:44.929
Their future was set
before they were even born.

21:44.929 --> 21:47.056
It's not fair. Ugh.

21:47.056 --> 21:48.724
Being pregnant
is giving me feelings.

21:48.724 --> 21:51.060
[ Chuckles ]

21:51.060 --> 21:55.314
So, uh, I went out
on a date with James.

21:55.314 --> 21:57.107
I thought you were
into Alonzo,

21:57.107 --> 21:58.984
the guy from
the community center?

21:58.984 --> 22:01.654
Uh, community center guy
is James.

22:01.654 --> 22:04.240
Alonzo is the guy that I hooked
up with on the camping trip.

22:04.240 --> 22:05.825
Damn.
I can't keep up.

22:05.825 --> 22:07.243
[ Chuckles ]
Me, neither.

22:07.243 --> 22:08.953
I was ‐‐ I was in a drought,
and now ‐‐

22:08.953 --> 22:10.704
It's raining men.
[ Chuckles ]

22:10.704 --> 22:13.457
I've always either been
in a relationship or married

22:13.457 --> 22:14.959
or undercover.

22:14.959 --> 22:16.919
I don't know.
It's kinda fun having options.

22:16.919 --> 22:18.420
[ Chuckles ]
[ Beeping ]

22:18.420 --> 22:21.131
And that's time.

22:21.131 --> 22:23.425
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

22:23.425 --> 22:27.096
Sandra: <i>Perhaps your son's</i>
<i>talents could be put to use</i>

22:27.096 --> 22:29.557
<i>in a less demanding field.</i>

22:29.557 --> 22:31.517
<i>Does he play video games?</i>

22:31.517 --> 22:33.853
Tomás:
<i>He's open to video games,</i>

22:33.853 --> 22:36.522
<i>but can one earn a living</i>
<i>doing that?</i>

22:36.522 --> 22:40.609
<i>There are guys that make so</i>
<i>much money playing video games</i>

22:40.609 --> 22:44.572
<i>that they never have a want</i>
<i>for the rest of their lives.</i>

22:44.572 --> 22:46.699
They're clearly not talking
about video games.

22:46.699 --> 22:49.368
No, she's making a play to take
over Madrigal's drug operation

22:49.368 --> 22:52.204
in exchange for
paying his son a royalty.

22:52.204 --> 22:53.956
[ Exhales sharply ]
That's a baller move.

22:53.956 --> 22:55.875
<i>How do I know</i>
<i>I can trust you?</i>

22:55.875 --> 22:59.420
<i>Because like you, I respect</i>
<i>the old ways of doing things.</i>

22:59.420 --> 23:01.630
<i>And don't you want to</i>
<i>leave this life knowing</i>

23:01.630 --> 23:04.800
<i>that no harm will ever befall</i>
<i>your only son?</i>

23:04.800 --> 23:06.927
♪♪

23:10.055 --> 23:12.016
Looking everywhere for you.

23:12.016 --> 23:13.267
What happened?
No, nothing.

23:13.267 --> 23:14.310
He's ‐‐
He's still in surgery.

23:14.310 --> 23:16.020
Abigail's just waiting
in the room.

23:16.020 --> 23:18.147
I just ‐‐
I needed to stretch my legs.

23:18.147 --> 23:20.441
No, I get it.
I get it. I get it.

23:20.441 --> 23:23.360
So, how's, uh, Roger?

23:23.360 --> 23:25.112
You mean Andrew?
Right, Andrew.

23:25.112 --> 23:26.780
It's...

23:28.240 --> 23:30.367
It's Roger, isn't it?
Is it?

23:30.367 --> 23:35.623
Okay, so, I just hope maybe
Roger is being good to you.

23:35.623 --> 23:36.916
Yeah, he is.

23:36.916 --> 23:39.084
Okay.
You deserve it.

23:40.878 --> 23:42.713
What?

23:42.713 --> 23:45.633
You and me [sighs]
dating other people.

23:45.633 --> 23:47.635
Right?
When does it stop being weird?

23:47.635 --> 23:50.095
Maybe it won't.

23:50.095 --> 23:52.514
I can't believe
we're back at a hospital.

23:52.514 --> 23:54.558
[ Birds chirping ]

23:54.558 --> 23:58.687
It seems like both yesterday
and a million years ago

23:58.687 --> 24:00.773
Henry went in
for his last surgery.

24:00.773 --> 24:03.484
He's a fighter.

24:03.484 --> 24:05.152
He's been fighting
since the day he was born.

24:05.152 --> 24:07.196
This is just another hill
for him to climb.

24:07.196 --> 24:09.949
He's gonna be fine.
I can feel it.

24:09.949 --> 24:11.533
[ Chuckling ]
Could you stop?

24:12.743 --> 24:13.744
Stop what?

24:13.744 --> 24:15.704
The compulsive optimism.

24:17.831 --> 24:19.124
It's exhausting.

24:19.124 --> 24:21.168
What do you mean?

24:21.168 --> 24:23.253
I‐I never told you this...

24:25.589 --> 24:29.343
...but every time our baby
went in for another surgery,

24:29.343 --> 24:31.595
I was convinced
we were going to lose him.

24:31.595 --> 24:33.764
Sarah, I always felt
the opposite.

24:33.764 --> 24:35.766
I know.

24:35.766 --> 24:37.142
But I couldn't go there.

24:37.142 --> 24:40.562
I had to protect myself,
every time,

24:40.562 --> 24:43.023
in case.

24:43.023 --> 24:45.192
It was like
flipping a coin.

24:45.192 --> 24:47.403
Another surgery,
another flip.

24:47.403 --> 24:49.071
And he always
comes up heads.

24:49.071 --> 24:50.447
But maybe this time
he won't.

24:50.447 --> 24:53.534
Maybe we should have opted
for the other surgery.

24:53.534 --> 24:54.952
♪♪

24:54.952 --> 24:57.496
Maybe this will wind up being
the worst day of our lives.

24:57.496 --> 24:58.664
Sarah...

25:00.290 --> 25:02.334
I can't think like that.

25:02.334 --> 25:03.961
And I can't think like you.

25:06.672 --> 25:08.841
I'm going back in.
[ Sighs ]

25:08.841 --> 25:10.467
You coming?
Right behind you.

25:10.467 --> 25:13.512
I'm gonna get
a little more fresh air.

25:13.512 --> 25:19.101
♪♪

25:19.101 --> 25:24.773
♪♪

25:24.773 --> 25:27.735
[ Exhales deeply ]

25:27.735 --> 25:33.699
♪♪

25:33.699 --> 25:36.744
[ Crying ]

25:41.749 --> 25:44.418
Tomás: <i>Selling video games</i>
<i>is a complicated business,</i>

25:44.418 --> 25:47.004
<i>especially for someone</i>
<i>new to town.</i>

25:47.004 --> 25:48.922
It's clear to us
that they're talking about

25:48.922 --> 25:51.341
her taking over
Madrigal's business...
Sandra: <i>Ah, but I have made...</i>

25:51.341 --> 25:53.302
...but a jury might not be able
to get past all the code.
<i>...some crucial connections</i>
<i>already.</i>

25:53.302 --> 25:54.178
Luckily,
they're gonna have to

25:54.178 --> 25:55.721
get into the details
at some point.

25:55.721 --> 25:58.474
There's no
second conversation.
<i>You'd be surprised.</i>

25:58.474 --> 25:59.767
This deal is getting made
today or not at all.
<i>You know how strong</i>
<i>my market share already is.</i>

25:59.767 --> 26:03.312
<i>I appreciate your diligence.</i>

26:03.312 --> 26:07.441
<i>One cannot be too careful where</i>
<i>family and money collide.</i>

26:07.441 --> 26:09.902
<i>But it's important to have</i>
<i>protection in place.</i>

26:11.195 --> 26:13.363
<i>And a good lawyer</i>
<i>is crucial.</i>

26:15.991 --> 26:19.036
<i>Have you ever heard of...</i>
<i>Wesley Evers?</i>

26:19.036 --> 26:20.621
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

26:20.621 --> 26:23.499
<i>He's made some interesting</i>
<i>connections of his own.</i>

26:23.499 --> 26:25.501
<i>I have someone vetting him</i>
<i>as we speak.</i>

26:25.501 --> 26:26.960
That's a threat.

26:26.960 --> 26:28.504
[ Cellphone beeps ]

26:28.504 --> 26:30.172
[ <i>Line ringing</i> ]

26:30.172 --> 26:31.799
[ Sighs ]

26:31.799 --> 26:33.967
♪♪

26:33.967 --> 26:35.344
Woman: <i>Hello?</i>
Who is this?

26:35.344 --> 26:37.387
I'm a nurse
in Dr. Etz's office.

26:37.387 --> 26:39.181
A patient's husband
left this phone here.

26:39.181 --> 26:42.059
I'm the patient. And a cop.
Where did he go?

26:42.059 --> 26:44.436
I don't know, but he left
in a hurry with a detective.

26:44.436 --> 26:46.522
A detective?
Wh‐‐ Did you hear a name?

26:46.522 --> 26:48.065
<i>No, but he said you sent him.</i>

26:48.065 --> 26:52.361
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

26:52.361 --> 26:53.612
You said Angela
needed to see me.

26:53.612 --> 26:55.572
Where is she?
Just up here.

26:55.572 --> 27:04.373
♪♪

27:04.373 --> 27:06.250
You're not a detective,
are you?

27:06.250 --> 27:07.501
[ Chuckles ]

27:07.501 --> 27:09.461
[ Whistles ]
[ Engine starts ]

27:09.461 --> 27:11.130
I was.

27:11.130 --> 27:14.383
A long time ago,
in Guatemala.

27:14.383 --> 27:18.428
I was like your Angela ‐‐
so desperate to do good.

27:18.428 --> 27:20.222
But so naive.

27:20.222 --> 27:23.559
♪♪

27:23.559 --> 27:26.019
I was made to understand
my failings the hard way.

27:26.019 --> 27:27.396
Let's just hope your Angela

27:27.396 --> 27:30.190
doesn't need to be
taught a lesson like I was.

27:32.651 --> 27:35.779
Listen to me.

27:35.779 --> 27:38.240
I have represented
hundreds of guys like you.

27:40.826 --> 27:42.953
You all think
that you're pure evil

27:42.953 --> 27:44.788
and willing to do
whatever your master asks,

27:44.788 --> 27:47.165
but you don't know anything
about Angela or me.

27:49.501 --> 27:52.379
If you hurt her,

27:52.379 --> 27:56.550
I will call in every favor
I am owed,

27:56.550 --> 27:59.219
and there's a lot.

27:59.219 --> 28:03.056
Rabid animals who will burn you
to your component molecules

28:03.056 --> 28:04.766
while you beg me for mercy.

28:04.766 --> 28:06.518
♪♪

28:06.518 --> 28:08.812
Do you hear me?

28:08.812 --> 28:11.273
[ Chuckles ]

28:11.273 --> 28:14.151
I love it.

28:14.151 --> 28:16.612
Such passion.

28:16.612 --> 28:18.822
Let's just hope you never
have to follow through, huh?

28:18.822 --> 28:25.078
♪♪

28:25.078 --> 28:27.539
Let's just hope
your beloved

28:27.539 --> 28:29.708
does the smart thing
for herself.

28:33.462 --> 28:35.339
And for your baby.

28:35.339 --> 28:38.091
♪♪

28:38.091 --> 28:39.801
[ Engine rumbling ]

28:39.801 --> 28:42.179
See you soon, <i>amigo.</i>

28:42.179 --> 28:44.806
[ Engine revs ]

28:47.851 --> 28:49.728
If she hurts Wesley ‐‐
She wouldn't dare.

28:49.728 --> 28:51.772
It's too reckless,
even for La Fiera.

28:51.772 --> 28:53.523
Alright,
backup's on the way.

28:53.523 --> 28:54.691
Security's scrubbing through
surveillance tapes.

28:54.691 --> 28:55.692
We'll find them.
[ Elevator bell dings ]

28:55.692 --> 28:57.653
Oh, thank God.

28:57.653 --> 28:58.654
Are you okay?
Yeah, I'm fine.

28:58.654 --> 29:00.113
Are you?

29:00.113 --> 29:01.990
Yeah.
What happened?

29:01.990 --> 29:03.659
I was just given
a not‐so‐subtle warning

29:03.659 --> 29:04.952
from your favorite
cartel boss.

29:04.952 --> 29:06.286
Did they hurt you?

29:06.286 --> 29:08.747
No, but they can
and they will.

29:08.747 --> 29:10.374
You should hand La Fiera off
to someone else,

29:10.374 --> 29:12.584
at least until
after the baby.

29:12.584 --> 29:14.836
I can't do that.

29:14.836 --> 29:17.673
Yes, you can.

29:17.673 --> 29:19.132
I just threatened
to go medieval on some guy

29:19.132 --> 29:20.968
if he even
looks at you funny.

29:20.968 --> 29:23.929
You did?
Of course.

29:23.929 --> 29:26.682
Is it bad that I'm a little
turned on right now?

29:26.682 --> 29:29.351
Angela,
it's not funny.

29:29.351 --> 29:31.311
I know.

29:31.311 --> 29:33.480
But if you know anything about
me, it's that I don't back down,

29:33.480 --> 29:35.691
and La Fiera just
overplayed her hand.

29:36.775 --> 29:37.943
Mack: Someone's happy.

29:37.943 --> 29:39.569
Today is a good day.

29:39.569 --> 29:40.821
Hey!

29:40.821 --> 29:42.406
Angela.

29:42.406 --> 29:43.991
You're about to get curb‐stomped
by a pregnant lady.

29:43.991 --> 29:45.784
Hey, hey, hey.
It's not worth it.

29:45.784 --> 29:47.703
<i>Hermana.</i>

29:47.703 --> 29:50.414
You know the baby feels
all the stress.

29:50.414 --> 29:51.832
It's no good.

29:51.832 --> 29:54.376
Maybe you should
take some time off.

29:54.376 --> 29:56.461
Get some rest.

29:56.461 --> 30:03.635
♪♪

30:03.635 --> 30:06.304
Think she bought it?

30:06.304 --> 30:08.557
Please tell me you got something
while we were out of pocket.

30:08.557 --> 30:10.892
Oh, yeah. They talked a lot
after you left.

30:10.892 --> 30:13.145
See, we now have a recording
of La Fiera

30:13.145 --> 30:15.772
making a deal to take over
Madrigal's operation.

30:15.772 --> 30:18.066
Yes.
Don't get too excited.

30:18.066 --> 30:20.402
It's just the first step
in making the case against her.

30:20.402 --> 30:23.196
The DA can't just rely
on a cryptic conversation.

30:23.196 --> 30:25.240
But this will
free up resources,

30:25.240 --> 30:26.908
maybe even
launch a task force.

30:26.908 --> 30:28.326
Definitely.

30:28.326 --> 30:30.203
And you'll want in, right?

30:31.747 --> 30:33.707
Who hired you
to smuggle the drugs?

30:33.707 --> 30:35.792
Technically, it was my idea.

30:35.792 --> 30:38.545
[ Sighs ]

30:38.545 --> 30:41.298
This has been
a really bad year.

30:41.298 --> 30:44.926
I lost my job,
had to drop out of school

30:44.926 --> 30:46.344
because I couldn't
afford tuition.

30:46.344 --> 30:48.472
Then I heard about
this dude willing to pay

30:48.472 --> 30:51.892
a small fortune
to move product to Ibiza, and...

30:51.892 --> 30:53.602
[ Monitor beeping ]

30:53.602 --> 30:55.979
It's just happy pills.

30:55.979 --> 30:58.315
Like, who was it gonna hurt,
you know?

30:58.315 --> 31:01.193
[ Sighs ]

31:01.193 --> 31:03.195
I'm so stupid.

31:03.195 --> 31:05.197
No, you just
made a mistake.

31:06.907 --> 31:09.242
Look, I'm not gonna lie and say
you can get off scot‐free,

31:09.242 --> 31:12.037
but we can put in a word
with the D. A.

31:12.037 --> 31:14.164
First offense,
intent to distribute ‐‐

31:14.164 --> 31:15.290
it shouldn't be too bad.

31:15.290 --> 31:16.625
You'd do that?

31:16.625 --> 31:19.044
<i>If</i> you tell us
who gave you the drugs

31:19.044 --> 31:21.713
and agree to testify
against them.

31:21.713 --> 31:24.424
Well, it just sounds like a
different way of possibly dying.

31:24.424 --> 31:26.343
Things can be done
to protect you.

31:26.343 --> 31:28.053
[ Beeping continues ]

31:28.053 --> 31:30.222
Can I think about it?
[ Stomach gurgles ]

31:30.222 --> 31:32.182
You have
until the drugs pass.

31:32.182 --> 31:33.183
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]
Uh, hey, hey!

31:33.183 --> 31:34.851
We need help in here!
Nurse?

31:34.851 --> 31:35.769
‐Coming in.
‐Yeah, we got her.

31:35.769 --> 31:37.771
What's happening?

31:37.771 --> 31:39.815
Could be an obstructed bowel, or
one of the drug packets broke.

31:39.815 --> 31:40.816
We gotta get her
into surgery.

31:40.816 --> 31:41.942
Alright. Let's go.

31:45.195 --> 31:47.280
I can't believe you were my age
when Henry was born.

31:47.280 --> 31:49.032
Babies having babies.

31:49.032 --> 31:51.034
Yeah, we were only married
a few months.

31:51.034 --> 31:52.452
Remember the house
we were renting?

31:52.452 --> 31:54.704
[ Chuckling ] Oh, my God.
You say "house."

31:54.704 --> 31:56.706
I say
"rotting wooden corpse."

31:56.706 --> 31:59.835
But you fixed it up,
worked 20‐hour days

31:59.835 --> 32:02.045
to get it all done in time
to bring Henry home.

32:02.045 --> 32:04.047
Yeah, and then we spent
two months at the hospital.

32:04.047 --> 32:07.134
Did you have any rituals
to help pass the time

32:07.134 --> 32:09.761
while you waited like this
for the surgeries to be over?

32:09.761 --> 32:12.264
I cried.
John did push‐ups.

32:12.264 --> 32:13.723
Actually, I think that was
the other way around.

32:13.723 --> 32:15.517
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, right, yeah.

32:15.517 --> 32:19.271
I got mad upper body strength
by the end of it.

32:19.271 --> 32:22.357
Henry didn't tell me
this could happen.

32:22.357 --> 32:23.984
He mentioned the TOF,
but he acted like

32:23.984 --> 32:25.527
it was all behind him.

32:25.527 --> 32:28.238
I'm sure
he believed it was.

32:28.238 --> 32:32.284
Still,
he owed you the truth.

32:32.284 --> 32:35.036
You deserve to know
what you're signing up for.

32:36.413 --> 32:37.873
I really hope I get to
tell him that.

32:37.873 --> 32:42.711
♪♪

32:42.711 --> 32:44.754
I will, right?

32:44.754 --> 32:46.339
He's gonna be okay?

32:49.467 --> 32:52.095
Yes. He is.

32:52.095 --> 32:53.972
♪♪

32:53.972 --> 32:56.224
[ Tires screech lightly ]

33:01.563 --> 33:03.356
Nice of you
to see us off.

33:03.356 --> 33:04.399
[ Car alarm beeps ]

33:04.399 --> 33:06.193
How's the knee?

33:06.193 --> 33:07.944
Doctor says it'll be a year
before I'm back out

33:07.944 --> 33:10.071
on the <i>fútbol</i> pitch.

33:10.071 --> 33:12.407
Don't skimp on
the physical therapy.

33:12.407 --> 33:13.783
It's gonna suck,
but if you push through it,

33:13.783 --> 33:15.035
you'll be glad you did.

33:15.035 --> 33:16.536
Thanks.

33:16.536 --> 33:18.455
Do you need a minute
with my mom?

33:18.455 --> 33:19.623
30 seconds.

33:19.623 --> 33:20.540
Okay.

33:22.042 --> 33:25.170
[ Clears throat ]

33:25.170 --> 33:27.339
Are you going to
threaten me again?

33:27.339 --> 33:30.759
No. I'm gonna give you
one last chance ‐‐

33:30.759 --> 33:32.928
for Diego's sake.

33:32.928 --> 33:35.597
Don't go through
with this deal.

33:35.597 --> 33:37.015
Fly home with your son.

33:37.015 --> 33:39.100
Take the money
you've already made

33:39.100 --> 33:41.102
and give him the life
he deserves,

33:41.102 --> 33:43.772
not the one
you think you're owed.

33:43.772 --> 33:45.899
<i>Hermana.</i>

33:45.899 --> 33:49.361
In my line of work,
you don't get to retire.

33:49.361 --> 33:52.822
There's no walking away,

33:52.822 --> 33:54.866
even if I wanted to.

33:56.826 --> 33:58.411
[ Vehicle door closes ]

33:58.411 --> 34:01.206
Which I don't.
[ Weapon cocks ]

34:01.206 --> 34:02.707
Gun!
[ Gunfire ]

34:02.707 --> 34:04.793
Diego!

34:04.793 --> 34:07.045
Diego!

34:07.045 --> 34:09.047
[ Gunfire ]
Go, go, go!

34:12.092 --> 34:14.469
[ Car alarms blaring ]

34:14.469 --> 34:22.644
♪♪

34:22.644 --> 34:31.152
♪♪

34:31.152 --> 34:32.779
Officer under fire.

34:32.779 --> 34:34.531
Parking garage, level four,
Shaw Memorial.

34:34.531 --> 34:37.284
At least three shooters.
Send backup.

34:37.284 --> 34:38.827
♪♪

34:38.827 --> 34:40.662
Diego, <i>por favor!</i>

34:40.662 --> 34:42.872
[ Breathing heavily ]
You have to let me get to him.

34:42.872 --> 34:44.708
You can't right now.
You can't.

34:44.708 --> 34:47.168
[ Gunfire, glass shatters ]

34:47.168 --> 34:49.462
[ Alarms continue blaring ]

34:51.548 --> 34:53.008
Oh.

34:53.008 --> 34:55.260
[ Gunfire and alarms continue ]

34:55.260 --> 35:01.600
♪♪

35:01.600 --> 35:07.689
♪♪

35:07.689 --> 35:09.107
I'll take these two.

35:09.107 --> 35:10.734
I got the big guy.

35:10.734 --> 35:12.444
Not that big.

35:14.237 --> 35:16.615
[ Gunfire ]

35:16.615 --> 35:24.080
♪♪

35:24.080 --> 35:31.546
♪♪

35:31.546 --> 35:33.131
Aah!

35:34.799 --> 35:36.801
Control, 7‐Adam‐19,
two in custody,

35:36.801 --> 35:37.761
one active shooter remaining.

35:37.761 --> 35:39.346
We need an RA.

35:39.346 --> 35:40.722
Hispanic male,
gunshot wound to the torso.

35:40.722 --> 35:41.973
Conscious and breathing.

35:43.683 --> 35:45.977
[ Gunfire ]

35:48.563 --> 35:49.606
[ Weapon cocks ]

35:49.606 --> 35:50.774
Drop the gun.

35:50.774 --> 35:52.150
Do it now.

35:53.818 --> 35:56.321
Arms out.

35:56.321 --> 35:58.615
Last suspect in custody.
Code 4.

35:58.615 --> 36:02.327
♪♪

36:02.327 --> 36:05.664
[ Breathing shakily ]

36:05.664 --> 36:09.542
[ Crying ] No!

36:09.542 --> 36:11.544
[ Sobbing ]

36:11.544 --> 36:14.255
Ahhhh!

36:18.093 --> 36:19.969
So...
And it was supposed to be
my day off.

36:19.969 --> 36:21.429
No good deed, sir.

36:21.429 --> 36:23.598
Any luck locating
Cesar Madrigal?

36:23.598 --> 36:26.059
Not yet. Odds are
he's gone to ground.

36:26.059 --> 36:27.352
It's not gonna help.

36:27.352 --> 36:28.645
He took a shot at the Queen
and missed.

36:28.645 --> 36:30.230
Yeah, well...

36:30.230 --> 36:31.648
[ Siren wailing,
police radio chatter ]

36:31.648 --> 36:33.149
Ma'am, I'm sorry.

36:33.149 --> 36:35.110
You can't come
into the crime scene.

36:35.110 --> 36:37.153
[ Radio chatter continues ]

36:37.153 --> 36:39.406
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

36:44.703 --> 36:46.079
[ Sniffles ]

36:47.247 --> 36:49.582
When will I have
my son's body to bury?

36:49.582 --> 36:51.126
In a few days.

36:51.126 --> 36:53.086
After the autopsy.

36:53.086 --> 36:55.130
[ Radio chatter continues ]

36:59.759 --> 37:03.138
Her son was her humanity.
With him gone...

37:03.138 --> 37:05.140
War is coming.

37:06.057 --> 37:09.561
[ <i>Muzak plays</i> ]

37:09.561 --> 37:10.854
Woman: <i>Angels West.</i>
<i>How can I help you?</i>

37:10.854 --> 37:12.897
Yes.
Uh, yes, hi.

37:12.897 --> 37:16.067
I would like to check the status
of an application for Colins.

37:16.067 --> 37:17.527
Tamara Colins.

37:17.527 --> 37:20.905
C‐O‐L‐I‐N‐S.

37:20.905 --> 37:22.782
Yes. Yeah.

37:22.782 --> 37:24.492
Ye‐‐ Okay.

37:24.492 --> 37:26.327
[ Chuckling ] Thank you.

37:26.327 --> 37:27.996
Oh, my gosh.
She's in.

37:27.996 --> 37:29.539
They're going to send Tamara
an e‐mail confirmation

37:29.539 --> 37:31.499
by the end of the week.
Well, tha‐‐ that's amazing.

37:31.499 --> 37:34.502
Mm‐hmm.
Y‐You're amazing,
and I am a suspicious idiot.

37:34.502 --> 37:36.838
No.
Well, maybe a little.

37:36.838 --> 37:38.631
Yeah.
You know what?

37:38.631 --> 37:40.717
I'm gonna talk to Tamara,
beg for forgiveness.

37:40.717 --> 37:43.136
No, you're not.
That would break her heart.

37:45.513 --> 37:47.974
‐How is she?
‐Lucky.

37:47.974 --> 37:49.726
A packet burst,
but only one pill ruptured.

37:49.726 --> 37:51.269
So we're keeping her overnight
to make sure

37:51.269 --> 37:52.395
there are no further
complications.

37:52.395 --> 37:54.189
Hey!

37:54.189 --> 37:56.983
Guys, I had
the weirdest dream.

37:56.983 --> 37:58.568
<i>You</i> were in it.

37:58.568 --> 38:00.904
Well, I hate to break it to you,
but that wasn't a dream.

38:00.904 --> 38:02.197
The flying monkeys
were real?

38:02.197 --> 38:04.199
Oh, uh...
You know what?

38:04.199 --> 38:06.159
Why don't we talk more
about this when you come down?

38:06.159 --> 38:08.703
Okay.
Okay.

38:08.703 --> 38:10.538
[ Both chuckle ]

38:10.538 --> 38:11.915
[ "Croire en rien" plays ]

38:11.915 --> 38:13.917
[ Sighs ]

38:13.917 --> 38:15.168
♪♪

38:15.168 --> 38:16.461
[ Sniffles ]

38:16.461 --> 38:22.842
♪♪

38:22.842 --> 38:23.843
Are you alright?

38:23.843 --> 38:26.304
[ Sighs ] I'm fine.

38:26.304 --> 38:28.890
So is the baby.

38:28.890 --> 38:31.935
But they killed Diego.

38:31.935 --> 38:33.853
La Fiera's son.

38:33.853 --> 38:35.021
♪ Pas besoin d'eux ♪

38:35.021 --> 38:36.981
Angela ‐‐
I know.

38:36.981 --> 38:41.236
But can we not talk about it
right now?

38:41.236 --> 38:43.696
There's still a lot of...

38:43.696 --> 38:46.991
paperwork and interviews.

38:46.991 --> 38:49.410
I'm not leaving
without you.

38:49.410 --> 38:51.204
Good.

38:51.204 --> 38:53.456
I don't want you to.

38:53.456 --> 38:54.958
[ Sniffles ]

38:54.958 --> 38:58.336
♪ Je sais que ça te fait mal ♪

38:58.336 --> 39:00.338
End of shift?

39:00.338 --> 39:03.007
[ Scoffs ]
More like end of job.

39:03.007 --> 39:04.259
They had to intubate
the old man.

39:04.259 --> 39:06.386
He'll be dead in a day or two,
so, um,

39:06.386 --> 39:08.179
I'm screwed again.

39:08.179 --> 39:10.265
[ Scoffs ]

39:10.265 --> 39:11.266
♪ Et même si tu insistes ♪

39:11.266 --> 39:13.101
You need to go
to rehab, Mack.

39:15.645 --> 39:18.523
Are you kidding?

39:18.523 --> 39:21.234
The pills are the only thing
moving me forward right now.

39:21.234 --> 39:23.903
I can't afford to stop.

39:23.903 --> 39:25.530
I'm too deep in the hole,

39:25.530 --> 39:27.490
and I gotta get out
before I can get clean.

39:27.490 --> 39:29.784
And how many times have you
heard a junkie say

39:29.784 --> 39:30.618
that exact same thing?

39:30.618 --> 39:33.204
Plenty.

39:33.204 --> 39:34.289
And how many of them
ever did?

39:34.289 --> 39:36.374
[ Scoffs ]

39:36.374 --> 39:37.959
None.

39:37.959 --> 39:42.213
Look, you can hate me
all you want, Mack,

39:42.213 --> 39:44.132
but I'm not
giving up on you.

39:44.132 --> 39:46.718
There's never an easy time
to get clean,

39:46.718 --> 39:49.637
and you are about to go through
the worst year of your life.

39:49.637 --> 39:52.056
You're not gonna survive this,
man, unless you're sober.

39:52.056 --> 39:54.726
You don't know that.
Yes, I do.

39:54.726 --> 39:56.394
Yes, I do.

39:56.394 --> 39:58.271
And so do you.

39:58.271 --> 39:59.898
Come on, Mack.

39:59.898 --> 40:01.733
It's time for you
to cowboy up, alright?

40:01.733 --> 40:04.986
Own your mistakes, man.
Just take your lumps.

40:04.986 --> 40:07.447
Be an example
for your kids.

40:07.447 --> 40:09.449
You're a better man
than this.

40:09.449 --> 40:13.411
♪ Mais même si tu insistes ♪

40:13.411 --> 40:14.787
♪ J'ai pu le goût
de croire en rien ♪

40:14.787 --> 40:16.247
Good. Alright?

40:16.247 --> 40:18.124
Okay.

40:18.124 --> 40:19.375
♪ Je serai le sauveur ♪

40:19.375 --> 40:20.960
[ Sobs ]

40:20.960 --> 40:22.962
Let's go.

40:22.962 --> 40:24.923
♪ De mon simple bonheur ♪

40:24.923 --> 40:27.550
Hey, you, uh ‐‐ you wouldn't
happen to have any suggestions

40:27.550 --> 40:30.678
on where I could throw
a bachelorette party, would you?

40:30.678 --> 40:33.640
I mean, Jason's got
that sports bar on Sunset.

40:33.640 --> 40:35.475
Yeah, that's a no‐go.
[ Sighs ]

40:37.435 --> 40:40.688
Oh, good.
Lasagna is in the oven.

40:40.688 --> 40:42.815
You cooked?

40:42.815 --> 40:45.109
I tried. I couldn't totally
remember my mom's recipe,

40:45.109 --> 40:46.903
but I think
it's pretty close.

40:46.903 --> 40:48.321
Oh, I got you something.

40:48.321 --> 40:50.323
[ Velcro ripping ]

40:50.323 --> 40:54.077
I know that Lucy broke
your Yoda thing.

40:54.077 --> 40:55.495
You told him, right?
Wh‐‐ Yes.

40:55.495 --> 40:57.288
‐Mm‐hmm.
‐Yes.

40:57.288 --> 40:59.999
Anyways, I couldn't afford
the fancy one, but...

40:59.999 --> 41:02.835
I thought you'd like this.

41:02.835 --> 41:04.921
‐Oh.
‐Aww.

41:06.589 --> 41:08.549
It's, uh...

41:08.549 --> 41:10.093
You did not
have to do that.

41:10.093 --> 41:13.346
I know, but you're letting me
stay here,

41:13.346 --> 41:16.099
and for the first time
in forever,

41:16.099 --> 41:18.685
I feel safe.

41:18.685 --> 41:21.062
Tamara, look, um...

41:21.062 --> 41:24.649
♪ Et le don de faire du bien ♪

41:24.649 --> 41:29.278
You are welcome to stay
as long as you want.

41:29.278 --> 41:31.364
Now [clears throat] have you
seen "The Mandalorian"?

41:31.364 --> 41:33.241
Because I am so down
to watch it again.

41:33.241 --> 41:34.117
‐For the third time.
‐Okay.

41:34.117 --> 41:35.451
That sounded judgy.

41:35.451 --> 41:36.953
Mm. [ Chuckles ]

41:36.953 --> 41:39.122
Sure.
It's based on a movie, right?

41:39.122 --> 41:41.040
A mo‐‐ Oh.
Shh. Relax.

41:41.040 --> 41:41.916
[ Chuckles ]
It's okay.

41:41.916 --> 41:43.459
Okay. Yep.
It's okay.

41:43.459 --> 41:45.336
Um, I gotta teach you
some stuff. Come on.

41:45.336 --> 41:48.423
What if he never
fully recovers?

41:48.423 --> 41:50.341
What if the future is
me being his nurse?

41:50.341 --> 41:51.884
You'll never be alone.

41:51.884 --> 41:53.553
Promise you that.

41:53.553 --> 41:55.680
[ Humming ]

41:55.680 --> 41:56.723
♪♪

41:56.723 --> 41:58.391
The surgery went really well.

41:58.391 --> 42:00.143
The damage wasn't as severe
as we thought,

42:00.143 --> 42:01.769
and Henry will make
a full recovery.

42:01.769 --> 42:04.313
Oh, thank God.
Thank you. Thank you.

42:04.313 --> 42:05.732
Um, w‐when
can we see him?

42:05.732 --> 42:06.941
Oh, in a few hours.

42:06.941 --> 42:08.192
They're just getting him settled
in recovery.

42:08.192 --> 42:09.193
Okay.
Thank you.

42:09.193 --> 42:10.862
Good night.

42:10.862 --> 42:13.281
‐[ Chuckles ]
‐Too soon for "I told you so"s?

42:13.281 --> 42:15.116
No, bring it on.
Okay. I told you so.

42:15.116 --> 42:17.160
[ Laughs ]
Come here.

42:17.160 --> 42:18.119
[ Chuckles ]
Get in here.

42:18.119 --> 42:19.162
Get in here.
Okay.

42:19.162 --> 42:20.538
♪ Du début à la fin ♪

42:24.375 --> 42:33.676
♪♪

42:33.676 --> 42:43.227
♪♪

42:43.227 --> 42:52.653
♪♪
